Leeds Contraception and Sexual Health Service (CaSH) provide a number of services to all age groups. As well as contraception, the drop-in clinics provide free services such as pregnancy testing, emergency contraception, testing for chlamydia and other sexually-transmitted infections, plus issuing free condoms. The team also offers friendly and confidential help and advice. Specialist IUD/IUS/Implant clinics are by appointment only after your initial consultation at one of the drop in clinics.

Opening times may be subject to change, please visit www.leedssexualhealth.com for up to date information.
